134
00:06:02,662 --> 00:06:04,865
This is perfect for me.

135
00:06:04,931 --> 00:06:07,868
Big glasses hurt your shoulder
while the small glass--

136
00:06:07,934 --> 00:06:10,070
Don't drink until your shoulder hurts.

137
00:06:10,136 --> 00:06:12,072
Our only muscles are in our shoulders.

138
00:06:12,138 --> 00:06:14,975
Right. All for beer.

139
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:17,043
-I guess you can work out with beer.
-Of course.

140
00:06:17,110 --> 00:06:18,979
We have to drink quickly.

141
00:06:19,045 --> 00:06:22,983
-Do you have non-alcoholic beer?
-We do.

142
00:06:23,049 --> 00:06:25,218
-I'll take one, please.
-Sure.

143
00:06:25,285 --> 00:06:27,354
-It's two against one today.
-You're in the middle.

144
00:06:27,420 --> 00:06:28,889
Let's merge.

145
00:06:30,891 --> 00:06:37,330
In the past,
Hokkaido was a barren land for sake.

146
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:38,331
I see.

147
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:40,634
But now,
Hokkaido rice is the most delicious.

148
00:06:41,001 --> 00:06:42,335
It's incredible.

149
00:06:42,402 --> 00:06:45,472
That's why sake made

150
00:06:45,538 --> 00:06:51,044
with Hokkaido rice…

151
00:06:51,978 --> 00:06:53,880
has recently become much better.

152
00:06:53,947 --> 00:06:55,849
-Right?
-Right.

153
00:06:55,916 --> 00:06:58,251
"Whisper of the Wind." That's a nice name.

154
00:06:58,351 --> 00:07:00,320
It was named by the owner
of Tokushaku Sanshiro,

155
00:07:00,387 --> 00:07:03,023
-a Solitary Gourmet filming location.
-Really?

156
00:07:03,089 --> 00:07:05,926
-I'd like to hear the whisper.
-You want to hear it?

157
00:07:05,992 --> 00:07:08,094
-We must try hearing that whisper.
-How fun.

158
00:07:08,161 --> 00:07:12,565
"Whisper of the Wind" could even work
as the title of his next single.

159
00:07:12,632 --> 00:07:15,135
-Let's listen to "Whisper of the Wind."
-Singing…

160
00:07:15,201 --> 00:07:17,037
You're like a radio DJ all of a sudden.

161
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:19,572
-Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

162
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,775
Jjan!

163
00:07:21,841 --> 00:07:23,076
One more time.

164
00:07:23,143 --> 00:07:25,912
-Jjan.
-Jjan!

165
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:41,761
Insanely good.

166
00:07:44,431 --> 00:07:46,232
It's still morning.

167
00:07:46,967 --> 00:07:49,869
This is otoshi, simple snacks.

168
00:07:49,936 --> 00:07:52,272
From now on, I'll be serving you
whatever I want.

169
00:07:53,268 --> 00:07:55,909
OTOSHI, FOUR DISHES
5,000 WON, 500 YEN, TABLE CHARGE INCLUDED

170
00:07:55,976 --> 00:07:58,845
